12/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The third meeting of the Stabilisation and Association Council -- between the EU and Macedonia-- was held Monday (December 11th) in Brussels. 
Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki, who led the Macedonian delegation, said the meeting focused on the country's pre-accession strategy -- regarding the Copenhagen criteria, progress in implementing the Stabilisation and Association Agreement, political and economic requirements, institutional reforms, the situation in the region and EU enlargement.
In its statement on the Western Balkans released on Monday, the EU Council expressed concern that the reform process has slowed this year in Macedonia. 
(EU press release, Makfax, MIA, A1 TV - 11/12/06)
